What are Services?

Services are programs that run in the background to provide functionality.

ğŸ‘‰ They start at boot or on demand
ğŸ‘‰ Managed by systemd

Examples:

sshd â†’ remote login

nginx â†’ web server

cron â†’ scheduled jobs

docker â†’ container engine

kubelet â†’ Kubernetes node agent

Service actions:
systemctl start sshd
systemctl stop nginx
systemctl restart docker
systemctl status cron


ğŸ“ Service definitions:

/usr/lib/systemd/system/
/etc/systemd/system/

Service flow:

Service â†’ Libraries â†’ Kernel â†’ Hardware

ğŸ’¡ Services keep the system alive and useful

ğŸ”— How Everything Connects (Very Important)
Example: SSH Login

1ï¸âƒ£ Service: sshd is running
2ï¸âƒ£ Config file: /etc/ssh/sshd_config
